‚Ä¢
I feel numb
And 
I feel vicious

I inhabit the shell of my body
And
My skin is too small

I go about amorphous
another day of nothing touching me
And
These feelings are too big
formless and crushing in their silence

A new name is added to the list of so many others
details heard
details forgotten
And
A new name is added to the pantheon
of brown bodies no one wants to
day-in and day-out
live in

Other than death
The one constant and absolute

